<p class="opt">Stock options are contracts that give employees the right to buy or exercise shares of company stock at 
    the grant price, which is a pre-set price. The grant price may also be called the strike price or the exercise
    price. Purchasing stock options is a time-limited benefit that has a deadline stated in the contract.</p>
