<h4>1. Bull Call Spread</h4>
<br/>
<p class="opt">A bull call spread is one of the bullish options strategies that involve buying one At-The-Money (ATM) call option and 
    selling the Out-Of-The-Money call option.<br/>
    <br/>
One should note that both the calls should have the same underlying stock and the same expiration date. <br/>
<br/>
In this strategy, profit is made when the price of the underlying stock increase which is equal to spread minus net debit 
and loss is incurred when the stock price falls which is equal to the net debit. Net Debit is equal to the Premium Paid for 
a lower strike minus the Premium Received for a higher strike. The Spread refers to the difference between the higher and 
lower strike price <br/>
<br/>
Bull Call Spread helps in protecting when the prices fall and the profit amount is also limited.</p>
<br/>

